<LI><P>&#147;Entrepreneurs and Ecosystems: Building Sustainable Economies,&#148; <I>Northwest Report</I>, January 1996: 10-15.</P>
<LI><P>Frenay, Robert.  1995.  &#147;Biorealism,&#148; <I>Audubon</I>, September/October: 70-73.</P>
<LI><P>Gablik, Suzy.  1992.  &#147;Socially conscious creativity helps heal society&#146;s ills,&#148; <I>Utne Reader</I>, March/April: 63-64.</P>
<LI><P>Geis, Don and Tammy Kutzmark.  1995.  &#147;Developing Sustainable Communities: The Future is Now,&#148; <I>Public Management</I>, August: 4-13.</P>
<LI><P>Gilman, Robert.  &#147;The Eco-Village Challenge,&#148; <I>In Context</I>, Issue 29.</P>
<LI><P>Glick, Daniel.  1996.  &#147;Cinderella Story: Chattanooga Transformed,&#148; <I>National Wildlife</I>, February/March: 42-45.</P>
<LI><P>Hubbard, Alice.  &#147;What are Sustainable Communities?,&#148; Rocky Mountain Institute, 1995.</P>
<LI><P>Josimovich, Lois.  1994.  &#147;The Return of the Village,&#148; <I>Sanctuary Magazine</I>, Massachusetts Audubon Society, March/April: 16-18.</P>
<LI><P>Kinsley, Michael and L. Hunter Lovins.  &#147;Paying for Growth, Prospering from Development,&#148; Rocky Mountain Institute, 1995.</P>
<LI><P>Kline, Elizabeth.  1996.  &#147;Why Sustainable Community Indicators? People Need A Reality Check,&#148; <I>Wingspread Journal</I>, Spring: 14.</P>
<LI><P>Maughan, Janet.  1996.  &#147;Sustainable Communities: An Idea Whose Time Has Come?,&#148; <I>Wingspread Journal</I>, Spring: 4-7.</P>
<LI><P>McNichol, Tom.  1992.  &#147;Earth savers: Ten ways to really save the planet,&#148; <I>Utne Reader</I>, March/April: 130.</P>
<LI><P>Meadows, Donella.  1991.  &#147;And justice for all: Four not-so-easy things you can do to save the planet,&#148;<I> Utne Reader</I>, March/April: 113.</P>
<LI><P>Morris, David.  1992.  &#147;Bringing the money back home: Local currency and barter foster stronger communities,&#148; <I>Utne Reader</I>, July/August: 42-44, 46.</P>
<LI><P>Morris, David.  1992.  &#147;Creativity thrives everywhere,&#148; <I>Utne Reader</I>, March/April: 65-66.</P>
<LI><P>Morris, David.  1992.  &#147;The four stages of environmentalism,&#148; <I>Utne Reader</I>, March/April:  159, 157.</P>
<LI><P>Nachman-Hunt, Nancy.  1995.  &#147;The &#145;Sustainable&#146; Debate,&#148; <I>The Boulder County Business </I><I>Report</I>, January: 1, 39-40.</P>
<LI><P>Rabinovitch, Jonas and Josef Leitman.  1995.  &#147;Urban planning in Curitiba: A Brazilian city challenges conventional wisdom and relies on low technology to improve the quality of urban life,&#148; <I>Scientific American</I>, March: 46-53.</P>
<LI><P>Salvesen, David.  1996.  &#147;Making Industrial Parks Sustainable,&#148; <I>Urban Land</I>, February: 29-32.</P>
<LI><P>Riggle, David.  1994.  &#147;Opportunities in Sustainable Development,&#148; <I>In Business</I>, November/December: 26-30.</P>
<LI><P>Schenk, Jim and Eileen.  1995.  &#147;The ecological neighborhood: Creating the sustainable urban community,&#148; <I>The Permaculture Activist 33, </I>December: 16-17.</P>
<LI><P>Steutville, Robert and David Riggle.  1995.  &#147;Outlook on Sustainable Enterprise,&#148; <I>In Business</I>, May/June: 18-22.</P>
<LI><P>&#147;Taming Urban Sprawl: Healthy Cities and Towns,&#148; <I>Northwest Report</I>, January 1996.</P>
