<H5 align=left>Adapted from Lane Council of Governments, 1995.</H5>

<!--end fig S.5-->
</td>
<td width=150 bgcolor="#FFFF99">
<!--sidebar p 7-->
<hr>
<P align=center>
"A community that does not scrutinize every significant 
proposal for new growth is gambling its 
future as surely as would a trip to Las Vegas 
with the municipal treasury. We can no longer 
heedlessly assume that any expansion will strengthen 
the community's economy."</P>

<H5>Michael Kinsely & 
Hunter Lovins,
Paying for Growth, 
Prospering From 
Development	
</H5><hr>
<!--end sidebar p 7-->
</td></tr></table>

