<head>
   <title>Success Stories</title>
   <meta name="GENERATOR" content="Mozilla/2.01Gold (Win32)">
</head>
<body text="#000000" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" link="#0000EE" vlink="#551A8B" alink="#FF0000" background="027.jpg">

<h2><a href="http://www.sustainable.doe.gov"><img src="/rsc/photow8.gif" alt="= CESD Home Page ="  align=left></a><a href="http://www.sustainable.doe.gov/ss/index.html"><img src="success.gif" border=2 height=44 width=160 align=left></a><font SIZE=-1><a href="http://www.sustainable.doe.gov/success.html">Renew
America Success Stories</a></font></h2><BR><BR><BR><BR><BR><BR>

<p>
<hr width="100%" ></p>

<h2><img src="eew_logo.jpg" hspace=3 border=0 height=200 width=454 align=bottom></h2>

<h2>Energy Efficiency Program</h2>

<address>Contact:</address>

<address>Mr. Paul A. Erickson, General Manager</address>

<address>City of Wahoo Utilities</address>

<address>605 N. Broadway</address>

<address>Wahoo, NE 68066</address>

<address>tel: (402) 443-3222</address>

<address>fax: (402) 443-5483</address>

<address>email: erickson@itec.net</address>

<address>No Internet Link Currently Available</address>

<address>
<br CLEAR="all"><img src="mrule.gif" alt=" " border=0 height=5 width=640></address>

<p><b><font SIZE=+2>Description</font></b></p>

<p>The Wahoo Utilities Energy Efficiency Program provides incentives to
all customers purchasing electricity from Wahoo Utilities to make improvements
to their homes and business buildings that will improve energy efficiency
without sacrificing comfort or convenience.</p>

<p>The program offers customers free energy audits to demonstrate what
improvements can be made to reduce energy costs. The audit also provides
a financial analysis of a wide range of energy savings options to help
identify the lowest life cycle cost option. Finally, Wahoo Utilities provides
financial incentives for the purchase of high-efficiency appliances and
technologies, including heat pumps, lighting and insulation.</p>

<p>The Energy Efficiency Program has served to reduce air pollution and
helped conserve natural resources such as coal and natural gas. In addition,
the program has helped many lower-income individuals make energy-efficiency
improvements they otherwise could not have afforded and the program has
provided Wahoo Utilities with the ability to utilize efficient demand-side
management of energy production.</p>

<p>Substantial energy and financial savings have been realized, in part
due to an aggressive education program, in a community that already had
the lowest electric rate in Nebraska and one of the lowest rates in the
country.</p>

<center><p><img src="mrule.gif" alt=" " border=0 height=5 width=640></p></center>

<p><b><font SIZE=+2>Program Highlights</font></b></p>

<ul>
<li>The program covers water heaters, furnaces, heat pumps, air conditioners,
insulation, water heater wraps, lighting, refrigeration, caulking and weather-stripping
and hot water pipe wraps.</li>

<li>Among other financial incentives, the program offers payments of 12.5
cents per cooling kilowatt hour saved and low-interest loans of up to $10,000.</li>
</ul>

<p><b><font SIZE=+1>Civic Center</font></b></p>

<ul>
<p>Wahoo Utilities is currently offering significant technical and financial
assistance in the design and construction of a major addition to the Wahoo
civic center, including an indoor swimming pool, jogging track, racquetball
courts and more.</p>
</ul>

<p><b><font SIZE=+1>Motel Construction</font></b></p>

<ul>
<li>Wahoo Utilities is currently offering significant technical and financial
assistance in the design and construction of a new motel for the community.</li>

<li>A lighting engineering study is being funded by Wahoo Utilities to
suggest state-of-the-art lighting applications.</li>

<li>Wahoo Utilities is funding the purchase and installation of an advanced
motel energy management system and costs for the first year's monitoring.</li>

<li>Wahoo Utilities obtained high-efficiency heat pumps for the rooms.</li>

<li>Wahoo Utilities is providing financial incentives to install efficient
lighting, windows, insulation and HVAC (heating, ventilating and air conditioning).</li>
</ul>

<center><p><img src="mrule.gif" alt=" " border=0 height=5 width=640></p></center>

<dl>
<p><b><font SIZE=+2>Vital Statistics</font></b></p>

<p><img src="mball.gif" alt="*" hspace=3 vspace=2 border=0 height=9 width=9><b>Program
Management/Partnerships: </b>The Energy Efficiency Program is managed by
Wahoo Utilities. Wahoo Utilities is working with trade allies and the local
school system to educate local residents about the environmental and financial
advantages of energy efficiency.</p>

<p><img src="mball.gif" alt="*" hspace=3 vspace=2 border=0 height=9 width=9><b>Budget:</b>
$168,000 total project cost.</p>

<p><img src="mball.gif" alt="*" hspace=3 vspace=2 border=0 height=9 width=9><b>Community
Served: </b>The nearly 2,000 residential and business customers of Wahoo
Utilities. Wahoo, Nebraska has a population of just under 4,000 people.</p>

<p><img src="mball.gif" alt="*" hspace=3 vspace=2 border=0 height=9 width=9><b>Measures
of Success:</b></p>
</dl>

<dl>
<dl>
<dl>
<li>Since the program began, nearly 350 residential audits have been completed
and energy efficiency work has been completed on 200 homes and nine commercial
buildings.</li>

<li>Participating residences have saved 350,000 KWH's (kilowatt hours)
of electricity and 65,000 natural gas therms.</li>

<li>Participating businesses have saved 78,000 KWH's.</li>

<li>The program saves more than 198 million BTU's (British thermal units)
annually.</li>

<li>Annual energy savings result in reduced energy costs of more than $45,000
a year, for a total return on investment in just under four years.</li>

<li>More than 100 efficient heat pumps have been installed, representing
a 5% market penetration in a very short time.</li>

<li>More than $640,000 in cash rebates and interest-free loans has been
provided to the community.</li>
</dl>
</dl>

<p><img src="mball.gif" alt="*" hspace=3 vspace=2 border=0 height=9 width=9><b>Contact</b>:</p>
</dl>

<dl>
<dl>
<address>Mr. Paul A. Erickson, General Manager</address>

<address>City of Wahoo Utilities</address>

<address>605 N. Broadway</address>

<address>Wahoo, NE 68066</address>

<address>tel: (402) 443-3222</address>

<address>fax: (402) 443-5483</address>

<address>email: erickson@itec.net</address>

<address>No Internet Link Currently Available</address>
</dl>
</dl>

<p><img src="mrule.gif" alt=" " border=0 height=5 width=640>
<br><i><font SIZE=-2>Success stories designed by Mark Nowak</font></i></p>

